  <p class=3D"txt-variant-label-short">
   =20
   =20
   =20
      of or relating to a system of numerical notation to the base 2, in wh=
ich each place of a number, expressed as 0 or 1, corresponds to a power of =
2. The decimal number 58 appears as 111010 in binary notation, since 58 =3D=
 1 =C3=97 2 5 + 1 =C3=97 2 4 + 1 =C3=97 2 3 + 0 =C3=97 2 2 + 1 =C3=97 2 1 +=
 0 =C3=97 2 0 .
